[SN]TITLE[SN]
Elderly woman dies in 'accidental' house fire in Wallasey

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
An elderly woman has died in a Wirral house fire believed to be accidentally started by "discarded smoking materials", the fire service said.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Fire crews were called to Rake Lane, Wallasey, at about midnight and found the woman's body in the lounge.
Merseyside Fire and Rescue Service (MFRS) said a sofa and flooring was damaged, with smoke damage throughout the building.
A fire safety campaign will now be carried out by MFRS in the area.
